{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a54bf2b6-24c9-4cc4-b7cf-6c4d50ec8ccd","content":"There's no repo here, so here's a general guide for the migration:\n\n### Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) doesn't use `vstest.console.exe`, so `VSTest@3` won't work. Use a script step instead:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n1. **Enable MTP in your test projects** — add to each test `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n   <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   ```\n\n2. **TRX reports** — MTP still supports the `trx` logger. Install the extension package:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Code coverage** — use `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` or add:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n4. **Publish results** — add separate publish steps:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishTestResults@2\n     inputs:\n       testResultsFormat: VSTest\n       testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n     condition: always()\n\n   - task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n     inputs:\n       summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n     condition: always()\n   ```\n\n### Summary\n\n- **Drop** `VSTest@3` → **use** `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (command: test) or a plain `script:` step.\n- Add `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` to your projects so `dotnet test` delegates to MTP.\n- Install `TrxReport` and `CodeCoverage` extension packages.\n- Publish TRX and coverage artifacts with the existing Azure DevOps tasks.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"15366b75-cdfe-4120-baeb-34d44bed4d62","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. This seems like a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":673,"requestId":"0BDE:155F80:20E183:269A86:69F00509"},"id":"34ea7532-1bd1-48ba-b0c6-fb87a9eabedc","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:53:42.411Z","parentId":"6f06882a-56c3-4367-abb1-7aacccd33b1c"}
